    "7846986": {
      "title": "Neurogenic factor-induced Langerhans cell activation in diabetic mice with mechanical allodynia",
      "abstract": "Background ::: Langerhans cells (LCs) are antigen-presenting dendritic cells located in the skin. It has been reported that LC activation is associated with painful diabetic neuropathy (PDN); however, the mechanism of LC activation is still unclear."
